Arthur V. As I posted earlier, you certainly have the right, as does Cook, to feel what you feel and think what you think. That even means if you want to take the time to &quot;analyze&quot; me, go right ahead.  If you want to be obsessed with me, study me, be fixated on me, go right ahead.  Let's just agree to not send each other a bill for consultation services, ok?<br><br>
In the meantime I am still around, still learning, still growing, still watching, and I still believe in this site. I still believe in the inherent goodness of most people. Hell even when Cook needs to call me &quot;the little commie&quot; now I can laugh. I used to flame. Then I learned. If you want it to be an act, Art, then it is an act, for you.  Enjoy it. I have found that I have a switch, like a throw-away bic lighter, and I don't have to flame.  I know, that is simple for most of you, but apparently it was not for me. I was way to quick to &quot;flic my bic&quot; many times in the past, only to wish I could have retracted that post the next day.  Finally I made my self a promise to think first, react second.  What is easy for one may not be for another.<br><br>
So Art, for whatever reason, I will be your field of study. And for Cook, the little Commie. And other things for other folks. That's all OK.  I know where I have been, where I am, but not where I am going. And ya know? That's ok too.
